# Numen UI Design Track — rules for this worktree

This worktree (`virtuna-ui-restrained`, branch `design/ui-restrained`) is the **UI design track** —
the restrained-accent rebrand (de-Claude). It runs in PARALLEL with an engine/backend rework in a
separate worktree (`virtuna-engine-rework`, branch `rework/engine-core`). Stay in your lane to avoid
conflicts. The prior design batch (`design/ui-system`) is already merged to `main` — branch off
`main`, not off the old branch.

## 1. Design system — trust ONE source
- The **only** authoritative design references are `src/app/globals.css` (the `@theme` token
  block) and `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`. Read `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` before any visual work.
- **IGNORE these — they are STALE** (they describe the retired Raycast/coral/glass system):
  `CLAUDE.md` "Raycast Design Language Rules" section, `BRAND-BIBLE.md`, `docs/tokens.md`,
  `docs/components.md`, `docs/design-specs.json`, `docs/usage-guidelines.md`,
  `docs/motion-guidelines.md`, `docs/brand/`.
- Current system = **flat-warm charcoal + cream text + RESTRAINED signal-red accent + matte**:
  - bg `#262624` (`--color-background`), cream text `#ece7de` (`--cream-primary`) — **never `#fff`**
  - accent = **signal red `#e23b2d`** (`--color-accent`), the logo mark — **terracotta `#d97757` is RETIRED** (it read too close to Claude). Never `#FF7F50`.
  - **ACCENT DOSAGE IS LOCKED — accent is a liveness signal, not paint.** Allowed: live dots, the lit constellation node, the brand mark, tiny active ticks. FORBIDDEN: primary buttons, icon buttons, skill pills, chevrons, placeholders, link floods, large fills. Read "Accent dosage (LOCKED)" in `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` before touching color.
  - **Primary actions are NEUTRAL cream** — use `--color-action` / `--color-action-foreground`, NOT the accent. (Composer send = cream button, dark glyph.)
  - accent-as-text on dark → `--color-accent-text` (`#ef6e62`); soft tint bg → `--color-accent-soft`. Solid-red fill glyph → `--color-accent-foreground` (cream).
  - `--color-accent` (brand red) ≠ `--color-error` (data/destructive red). Never conflate.
  - borders 6% (`rgba(255,255,255,0.06)`), hover 10%
  - **matte only**: no glass gradients, no glow, no white inset-shine. Flat + border + (rarely) `--shadow-float`.
  - Inter for all chrome; serif (`--font-serif`, Newsreader; Fraunces candidate) **only** for voice-moments (greeting/hero).
  - radius 4/6/8/12/16/20/24 — cards 12, inputs/buttons 8.
  - **Identity is carried by the constellation/SIM motif + serif voice + copy**, since color is now quiet. Invest there.
- **Always consume tokens, never hardcode hex.** No `#FF7F50`, `#07080a`, `#18191a`, `#fff`, no raw `#d97757`/`#e23b2d` in components.
- Keep `src/components/reading/__tests__/reskin-matte.test.ts` GREEN (guards against coral/glass).

## 2. File ownership — DO NOT cross
- ✅ **You own:** `src/components/**`, page-level styling/layout in `src/app/(app)/**` (NON-api),
  `src/app/globals.css`, design tokens, `src/types/design-tokens.ts`.
- ⛔ **Do NOT touch (engine track owns these):** `src/lib/**`, `src/app/api/**`, runners,
  engine, `supabase/**`, prompt/KC files. If a UI change seems to need a backend change,
  STOP and flag it — don't edit backend here.

## 3. Coupled surfaces — visual-only, don't change contracts
`AudienceLens`, the composer, and the thread skill-cards are being reworked on the engine side
(their data shape/props may change). For these you MAY restyle/relayout, but **do NOT change the
props/data contracts** they consume or the block schemas. Structural changes to these wait for
the engine rework — coordinate first.

## 4. Conflict hygiene
- Rebase onto `origin/main` frequently (`git fetch origin && git rebase origin/main`).
- Keep PRs small and per-surface; merge often to minimize drift.
- Commit format `type(surface): description`. Atomic commits.

## 5. Verify before done
- `npm run lint` + typecheck clean.
- Visual check in the browser (or screenshot) for any surface you change.
- Don't say "should work" — show it.
